column1: In order to make the different generation data consistent throughout trend and time development, we have scaled the generation data by 2020 capacities.
For the Baltic countries we have fixed capacities and generation data from 1991 for all the preceding years.
Germany before 1990 is just the sum of generation (and sum of capacities) of West and East Germany.
Czech Republic and Slovakia before 1993 are distributed according to share of capacities in 1993.
Former Yugoslavia/Serbia and Montenegro is distributed according to shares of capacities in 1992/2006/2008.
